<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="446" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,575,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,647,672]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The genus is mainly diagnosed by its male genitalia where the valva is divided into distal costal and saccular process, absence of the medial costal process which is present in some other related genera of the subtribe Nudariina Walker (e.g., 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker" authorityName="Walker" box="[439,621,719,744]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Barsine" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[439,526,720,743]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Barsine</emphasis>
Walker
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Moore" authorityName="Moore" box="[638,803,720,743]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Nepita" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[638,713,720,743]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Nepita</emphasis>
Moore
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Felder" authorityName="Felder" box="[820,971,719,744]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Cyme" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[820,884,720,743]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Cyme</emphasis>
Felder
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler" authorityName="Butler" box="[988,1205,719,744]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Melanaema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[988,1120,720,744]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Melanaema</emphasis>
Butler
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker" authorityName="Walker" box="[1222,1382,719,744]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Asura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1222,1290,720,743]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Asura</emphasis>
Walker
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Holloway" authorityName="Holloway" box="[151,413,756,781]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Quadrasura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,288,756,780]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="446">Quadrasura</emphasis>
Holloway
</taxonomicName>
); vesica has large, well separated cornuti, their number may vary from single cornutus to many, prominent, well formed, long spines. Female genitalia with extensive fields of long spines (
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway" box="[1253,1432,791,816]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2001) The moths of Borneo: family Arctiidae, subfamily Lithosiinae. Malayan Nature Journal, 7, 279 - 486." type="journal article" year="2001">Holloway 2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirti" box="[151,373,828,853]" pageId="1" pageNumber="446" refString="Kirti, J. S. &amp; Singh, N. (2016) Arctiid Moths of India, 2. Nature Books India, New Delhi, pp. 1 - 214." type="journal article" year="2016">Kirti &amp; Singh 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
